spec.step_function:
Let val = grid[ant.row][ant.col].
1. Turn rule  (deterministic tie-break):
    if val is EVEN (0 or 2) turn LEFT  (dir = (dir+3) mod 4)
    if val is ODD  (1 or 3) turn RIGHT (dir = (dir+1) mod 4)
2. Rotor update: grid[ant.row][ant.col] = (val+1) mod 4  // clockwise rotation
3. Move: ant.row = (ant.row + dRow[dir]) mod H;
         ant.col = (ant.col + dCol[dir]) mod W   where dRow=[-1,0,1,0] and dCol=[0,1,0,-1].
All steps are applied **simultaneously** to every cell only through the single ant, therefore no further tie-breakers are required.

